        <mxCell id="wjWPv7xuz2TdYhpFKJe6-5" value="&lt;h1&gt;Actions To Consider&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to limit your phone or social media use (or you have tried and failed), here are some tips:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Try taking small easy steps at first, which don&#39;t intrude on your life. Taking a step to not use your phone 30 mins before bed will be excruciatingly difficult when that&#39;s what you do before bed. A more reasonable first action would be to not bring your phone into the bathroom, and yes, it will be boring. That&#39;s the reality if you really want to limit what experiences involve your phone.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;Start by tracking your use, instead of changing it. This will make you more aware of if your phone use is an issue, and if it is, how much. It&#39;s up to you make the call of what is too much.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: initial;&quot;&gt;An app I recommend to track your usage is StayFree (iOS &amp;amp; Android), which you can also set up limits in the future if you are interested in doing that sort of thing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="120" width="360" height="320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wjWPv7xuz2TdYhpFKJe6-8" value="&lt;h1&gt;Self-Questionnaire&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here is a series of questions to ask yourself which may help you determine how much of an issue your phone/social media use is:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Realistically, how much time do you spend on your phone each day?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Think of 3 things that occur commonly while using your phone that you makes you react positively in the moment. (i.e. joy, happiness, pride, fulfillment, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Now think of 3 more common things while using your phone that make you react negatively in the moment. (i.e. sadness, loneliness, worthlessness, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=12;fontColor=#000000;" parent="1" vertex="1">
